               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430703-name-561" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430703-name-561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430703-name-561" type="surname" value="GOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430703-name-561" type="given" value="WILLIAM AUGUSTUS"></interp>WILLIAM AUGUSTUS GOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barman to Mr. John Watson, who keeps the Angel public-house, in Chapel-street, Westminster. On the night of the 27th of June I served a customer at the end of the bar—the prisoner was at the bar—he made a snatch at a pile of silver on the sideboard—he had no business there—I saw the money in his hand—he ran away—I ran after him and caught him—just as he got by the door he threw the money on the floor—some person picked it up and gave me fourteen sixpences and one fourpenny piece—I saw it picked off the floor—the prisoner resisted and tried to get away—I held him tight, brought him inside, and gave him in charge—I went to the 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. worth of silver and there was 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. gone.</p>
